    <h2 id="ï¸-task-4-mount-and-inspect-iso-images-linux">âš™ï¸ Task 4: Mount and Inspect ISO Images (Linux+)</h2>
  </li>
  <li>Linux+: Manage media, mount and inspect ISO images</li>
  <li>Use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">mount</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">isoinfo</code> to inspect contents of a downloaded ISO</li>
  <li>Mount a virtual CD-ROM to a VM and check logs using <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">lsblk</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dmesg</code></li>
  <li>Unmount media and clean up temporary mounts</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">mount</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">umount</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">isoinfo</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">lsblk</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">dmesg</code></li>
  <li>Markdown: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">iso-inspection-log.md</code></li>
  <li>Screenshot: ISO mount and contents
